Cac.name: Create Channel or Category
Cac.usage: createcc|ccc <name> <text/voice/category> (cateogry new channel will be in)
Cac.help: Creates a new text channel, voice channel or category. Note that the cateogry arg will not be required if you are creating a category.

Cac.name: Delete Channel or Cateogry
Cac.help: Deletes a text channel, voice channel or category.

Cac.name: Pin
Cac.help: Pins a message with message link or id

Cac.name: Unpin
Cac.help: Unpins a message with message link or id

Cac.name: Edit Channel
Cac.usage: editchannel|ec <attribute to edit/member or role> <attribute value/permissions:True, False or None>

Games.name: YesNoMaybe
Games.help: Answers questions with Yes, No and Maybe.

Games.name: Hack
Games.help: Hacks into a members account and steals all their information.(Not really)

Games.name: Flipcoin
Games.help: Using this command you can either flip a coin by yourself or, challenge another player to flip a coin with you.

Games.name: Encrypt
Games.help: This command currently uses two types of encoding languages to encrypt a sample of text

Games.name: Decrypt
Games.help: This command decrypts messages in code and morse.

Misc.name: Ping
Misc.help: Gets latency of the reply time of the bot in milliseconds

Misc.name: Leap
Misc.help: Checks whether or not a given year is a leap one.

Misc.name: Palindrome
Misc.help: Checks whether or not a snippet of text is a palindrome.

Misc.name: Wikipedia
Misc.help: Searches wikipedia and returns info based on a given query.

Misc.name: Dictionary
Misc.help: Searches the internet and returns definitions, synonyms and antonyms.

Misc.name: Time to
Misc.help: Returns the countdown to the given timestamp.

Misc.name: Covid Data
Misc.help: Returns covid statistics for the whole world or a country

Mslo.name: Invite
Mslo.help: Invites people from outside the server. This can vary from user to user based on their privacy settings.

Mslo.name: Kick
Mslo.help: Kicks members from the server. Owners of servers have an option to skip the conformation message as well use the kick command when it is de-activated, to access this, type: "override 403" in the place of reason.

Mslo.name: Ban
Mslo.help: Bans members from the server. Owners of servers have an option to skip the conformation message as well use the ban command when it is de-activated, to access this, type: "override 403" in the place of reason.

Mslo.name: Unban
Mslo.help: Unbans users from the server and invites them by looking through the servers bans list.

Music.name: Summon
Music.help: Summons the bot to a voice channel. If no channel was specified, it joins your channel.

Music.name: Leave
Music.help: Clears the queue and leaves the voice channel.

Music.name: Volume
Music.help: Sets the volume of the player.

Music.name: Stop
Music.help: Stops playing song and clears the queue.

Music.name: Skip
Music.help: Vote to skip a song. The requester can automatically skip. 3 skip votes are needed for the song to be skipped.

Music.name: Queue
Music.help: Shows the player's queue. You can optionally specify the page to show. Each page contains 10 elements.

Music.name: Remove
Music.help: Removes a song from the queue at a given index.

Music.name: Loop
Music.help: Loops the currently playing song. Invoke this command again to unloop the song.

Music.name: Play
Music.help: Plays a song. If there are songs in the queue, this will be queued until the other songs finished playing. This command automatically searches from various sites if no URL is provided.

Python.name: PyPi
Python.help: Provide information about a specific package from PyPI.

Roles.name: Create Role
Roles.help: Creates a role with a default name "New role"

Roles.name: Add Role
Roles.help: Adds a role onto a member.

Roles.name: Remove Role
Roles.help: Removes a role from a member.

Roles.name: Edit Role
Roles.usage: editrole|er <role> <the attribute to be edited> <val of attr>
Roles.help: Edits a role. In the "val of attr" slot, you type Numbers for Heirarchy, True/False for Permissions and displaying members seperately and Alphabets for Name

Roles.name: Add to all
Roles.help: Adds one role to all members

Settings.name: Enable
Settings.help: Enables the selected setting the bot has for the server.

Settings.name: Disable
Settings.help: Disables the selected setting the bot has for the server.

Settings.name: Set Prefix
Settings.help: Sets the prefix for the server the command is called in.

Settings.name: Settings
Settings.help: Shows the current settings of the server.

Sports.name: Ipl score
Sports.help: Gets the score of the next or live IPL match

Sports.name: Ipl table
Sports.help: Gets the IPL table, or table statistics of a team based on your input

Utilities.name: Clear
Utilities.usage: clear|cl (amt of msgs to be deleted)
Utilities.help: Deletes any number of messages below 20.

Utilities.name: Calculator
Utilities.help: Calculates and gives result based on input. If 'help arith' or 'help compare' is put in the expression argument, you'll get a list of Operators.

Utilities.name: Change nickname
Utilities.help: Changes the nickname of a given Member.

Utilities.name: Member Info
Utilities.help: Displays the info of a given Member.

Utilities.name: Error Code List
Utilities.help: Gives a list of error codes that the bot gives out in an error, and the codes' meanings.

Utilities.name: Delinvs
Utilities.help: Deletes all active invites of the server.

Utilities.name: Status
Utilities.help: Displays the Status of a given member

Utilities.name: Add bot to server
Utilities.help: Generates and sends a link to add the bot to your server

Utilities.name: Announce
Utilities.help: Announces to every member in the server.

Utilities.name: Member List
Utilities.help: Returns a member list of everyone in the server.

Utilities.name: Define
Utilities.help: Writes a defining statement to a selected channel
